[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T14:13:10+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Blizzard Entertainment\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/warcraft-2-cover-crop.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">An update pushed to Blizzard\u2019s internal servers the evening of November 5 indicates a remastered version of <em>Warcraft 2: Tides of Darkness</em> may be waiting just over the horizon, <a href=\"https://www.wowhead.com/news/warcraft-ii-remastered-internal-alpha-new-blizzard-catalog-entry-added-349660\">Wowhead reports</a>.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The data, <a href=\"https://blizztrack.com/view/w2rd?type=versions\">publicly</a> <a href=\"https://blizztrack.com/config/w2rd/pc/25a63b003070197f83bf54d2c82a9429\">viewable</a> on automated Battle.net update logger Blizztrack, refers to an internal alpha and includes artwork and a ", "id": 1466438, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/world-of-warcraft/475344/warcraft-2-remastered-leak", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "A remastered Warcraft 2 may be in the works", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T13:20:23+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/Untitled-design-2024-11-06T105335.042.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>Dragon Age: The Veilguard</em> is a game about building a team to fight ancient elven gods, but the more time I spend in Thedas, the more I realize that I\u2019d rather be chasing a different villain. Elgar\u2019nan and Ghilan\u2019nain are two of the ancient elven pantheon known as the Evanuris, and they\u2019re up to no good \u2014 blighting villages, murdering innocents, and trying to restore their ancient empire. But I find that a total snooze compared to the game\u2019s real villainous star: Johanna Hezenkoss, evil lich in progress and absolute queen.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">I should probably explain why I\u2019m not worried about the Evanuris, despite the ", "id": 1465935, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/475181/dragon-age-veilguard-best-villain-emmrich-hezenkoss", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Dragon Age: The Veilguard\u2019s best villain is found in a side story", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T12:52:17+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A person falls off what looks like a cliff.\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Devolver Digital\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/babysteps-falling.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>Baby Steps</em>. I haven\u2019t stopped thinking about the \u201cliteral walking simulator,\u201d as the devs describe the project, since it was <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23754090/baby-steps-game-release-date-announcement-trailer\">first revealed</a> by publisher Devolver Digital last June. All we\u2019ve seen of <em>Baby Steps</em> between then and now are two <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pJZNBD2SwTs\">additional</a> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D5aN5uprpAk\">videos</a> driving home the difficult, physics-based gameplay and humorous story. As such, I can\u2019t help but wonder if <em>Baby S", "id": 1465936, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/475194/baby-steps-release-date-2024", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Where the heck is Baby Steps?", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T12:30:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/ss_e17186b3f68ba9ed8da9e64d35cc505a9c1ed75d.1920x1080.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Being lost in a dark and unfamiliar location is a common fear, and a great start to a horror game. Filling that place with weird, menacing monsters is even better. One horror game adds another novel twist to the formula: I have no idea what anyone is saying, and I have to piece this strange, foreign language together before I\u2019m viciously murdered. Welcome to <a href=\"https://store.steampowered.com/app/2302660/Homicipher/\"><em>Homicipher</em>, a \u201cfemale-targeted language deciphering and exploration ADV based on the concept of \u2018romance with horror men.</a>\u2019\u201d I\u2019ve never played anything like it.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">", "id": 1465483, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/475185/homicipher-review-impressions-pc", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Homicipher is a clever horror game about female desire and monster language", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T12:13:34+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/nintendo-music.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">When Nintendo <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/news/472881/nintendo-music-app-android-ios\">announced its new music app</a> last week, I excitedly downloaded it onto my phone. I thought I would finally be able to listen to <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/gaming/465087/zelda-echoes-of-wisdom-music-rules\">the superlative score for <em>The Legend of Zelda: Echoes of Wisdom</em></a> without resorting to rips on YouTube.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">I was wrong. It wasn\u2019t there. Nor were the soundtracks to <em>Tears of the Kingdom</em>, or <em>The Wind Waker</em>, or <em>A Link to the Past</em>. No <em>Super Mario World</em> or <em>Super Metroid</em>. No F-Zero or", "id": 1465484, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/opinion/475085/nintendo-music-app-review", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Nintendo Music is a very Nintendo streaming service", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A gray-haired player character in Dragon Age: The Veilguard reflects upon their identity. The text prompt on the screen says &quot;establish trans identity.&quot;\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: BioWare/Electronic Arts via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/Dragon-Age-The-Veilguard-Screenshot-2024.10.17-20.33.52.06.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Even going beyond the very expansive character creator, <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/review/470712/review-dragon-age-the-veilguard-ps5-xbox-pc\"><em>Dragon Age: The Veilguard</em></a><em> </em>includes a whole range of ways to <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/gaming/472513/dragon-age-veilguard-trans-nonbinary-identity-role-play\">role-play a gender-diverse character</a>, especially when it comes to dialogue choices. It\u2019s", "id": 1465485, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/474954/dragon-age-the-veilguard-gender-trans-nonbinary-interview", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Why the Dragon Age: The Veilguard team designed its trans-inclusive storylines", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T10:30:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/METAL-GEAR-SOLID-3-SNAKE-EATER-EVA.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">For the past 20 years, the identity of the woman behind EVA in <em>Metal Gear Solid 3: Snake Eater</em> has been a closely guarded secret. The actor credited with the role is Suzetta Mi\u00f1et, but that name is a pseudonym for a much more famous voiceover artist, a new video from Konami promoting the upcoming <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23351764/metal-gear-solid-3-remake-release-date-trailer-announcement\"><em>Metal Gear Solid 3</em> remake</a> reveals.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The third episode of the Metal Gear Solid Legacy Series, hosted by David Hayter, reveals that the actor behind EVA (aka Tatyana) in <em>Snake Eater</em> is Jodi", "id": 1465068, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/475091/metal-gear-solid-3-eva-voice-actor-revealed", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The secret actor behind Metal Gear Solid 3\u2019s EVA has been revealed after 20 years", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T10:15:06+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/DTDsteamdeckrecording.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Steam\u2019s <a href=\"https://store.steampowered.com/gamerecording\">game recording capabilities</a> are now available on PC and on <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/reviews/23950861/steam-deck-oled-review-valve-handheld-gaming\">Steam Deck</a> following a beta period. The suite of features offer a ton of flexibility that compete with other PC game clipping software, notably the GeForce Experience that\u2019s offered by Nvidia. This includes the basics that most people would expect, like auto recording or manual clipping through keyboard hotkeys. But it goes further, with easy access to replays via the Steam overlay and intuitive exporting of clips via QR codes that you c", "id": 1464662, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/475098/steam-game-recording-pc-deck-features", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Steam\u2019s new recording features allow deep integration with games", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T09:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Marvel vs. Capcom: Infinite &amp; Beyond team/Capcom\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/GXkQjoTbUAATWGa.jpeg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">For more than 25